From 75f8b5510799078d93eaaa9acb80b7b22184c542 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: DNN-Opt Developer <dnnopt@example.com>
Date: Thu, 23 Apr 2026 14:58:25 +0800
Subject: [PATCH] feat: Add DNN-Opt integration for AArch64 GEMM optimization
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

This patch integrates DNN-Opt v2.5 with oneDNN v3.7 to provide
optimized GEMM kernels for AArch64 platforms.

Key changes:
- cmake/dnnopt.cmake: New cmake module to find and link DNN-Opt
- cmake/options.cmake: Add DNNL_AARCH64_USE_DNNOPT option
- CMakeLists.txt: Include dnnopt.cmake after blas.cmake
- src/cpu/gemm/gemm.cpp: Dispatch to dnnopt before stride check
- src/cpu/aarch64/dnnopt_gemm_wrapper.hpp: Duality transform wrapper

Technical details:
- dnnl_sgemm swaps M↔N and A↔B before calling extended_sgemm
- This causes stride mismatch for non-square matrices
- Solution: Use implicit transpose via duality transform
- Col-major data read as row-major gives natural transpose

Build:
  cmake -DDNNL_AARCH64_USE_DNNOPT=ON -DDNNOPT_ROOT=/path/to/dnnopt ..

Performance (Neoverse N2, K=4096):
  M=1:    17.5 GFLOPS (baseline: FAILED)
  M=64:   36.6 GFLOPS (baseline: FAILED)
  M=512:  44.9 GFLOPS (baseline: FAILED)
  M=1024: 40.0 GFLOPS (baseline: 61.3 GFLOPS)

Co-Authored-By: Claude Opus 4.6 <noreply@anthropic.com>
